Ray Liotta, the actor known for his roles in "Field of Dreams" and the Martin Scorsese mob classic "Goodfellas," died at the age of 67, it was reported on Thursday, May 25. Liotta's many film and television credits include "John Q," "Blow," "Operation Dumbo Drop," "Shades of Blue" and "Unbreakable Kimmy Schmidt." More recently, Liotta narrated the TV docuseries "The Making of the Mob" and starred in "The Many Saints of Newark," the prequel film to the hit television mob series "The Sopranos."